  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\n<!--     https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md -->\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\n<!--   * Read the debugging docs: https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/HowTo/Monitor/Logging/ -->\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3Ahyperledger/Besu -->\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\n\n### Description\nBesu's engine api should separately catch and handle underlying exceptions (such as storage exceptions) and failures that are unrelated to block execution/validation.  Rather than presuming that any exception during block processing translates into an `INVALID` response.\n\nFor example, on mnsf-12,  the lighthouse-besu-2 node built and proposed a block, but on the subsequent engine_newPayload execution of the proposal, encountered a RocksDB timeout.  This timeout exception was interpreted as a bad block and we incorrectly responded to CL with `INVALID`\n\n[https://app.zenhub.com/files/206414745/25826dce-f9b5-416e-b9df-601835c1331f/download](https://app.zenhub.com/files/206414745/25826dce-f9b5-416e-b9df-601835c1331f/download)\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n* engine-api should correctly discriminate between validation and execution failures rather than underlying exceptions such as rocksdb storage exceptions.\n\n",
